<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-26"><hi rend="italic">January 26,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Snyder reports that in Colombia’s official circles a rumor is
                            current, as coming from Reyes, that the Government of the United States
                            has retreated from its position and will permit the landing of Colombian
                            troops at Panama, and states that it is from this motive that Colombian
                            forces are being organized. He requests to be advised as to the
                            situation.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>